analysis:
From last week (2025-08-04 to 2025-08-10), the sentiment surrounding BABA was mixed, with a slightly positive leaning. There were neutral reports about market trends, company announcements, and analyst ratings. Some negative news included concerns about regulatory scrutiny for Ant Group and potential closures of some stores. Positive developments included benchmark maintaining a buy rating and the launch of new AI models.

This week (2025-08-11 to 2025-08-15), the sentiment has been predominantly negative. Key risks include downbeat economic data in China, concerns about tariffs, and regulatory scrutiny of companies like Ants Bright. There is also a negative sentiment related to Tencent's cautious AI spending and potential risks to Alibaba and JD.com from the food delivery war. Positive developments include JD.com's earnings beat and strong ad spending in China.

Sentiment Outlook: Negative
